- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the study of graph classes characterized by forbidden induced subgraphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper analyzes the complexity of the Graph Isomorphism problem on various graph classes, which is a topic in computational complexity.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computational geometry, the study of graph classes and their structural properties is often related to computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper develops techniques for the structural analysis of graph classes, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The study of graph classes and their properties is also relevant to game theory, as graphs are often used to model games and strategic interactions.
